==English==

===Etymology===

Viti (Latin for Vine) and Culture (to grow).

===Noun===
'''viticulture'''

#Growing [[grape]] vines.
#:''The old French farmer practiced '''viticulture''' and raised some of the best grapes in the world. He was knowledgable in '''viticulture'''.''
